modules.description: This module enables generic programming through GADT-based runtime type representations, supporting operations like serialization, equality checking, and structured data transformations. It works with OCaml's primitive types, recursively-defined algebraic data types, and compound structures like records and variants, using combinators to build type representations directly in code. Specific applications include JSON encoding/decoding, binary serialization, and efficient manipulation of complex data structures without intermediate format conversions.
